means: 教会委员，陶制的长烟斗

sentence.Network_en: Church of England an assistant to the churchwarden ; collects offerings of money in the church.
sentence.Network_cn: (英国国教)教会执事的帮手; 在教会中募集捐献供品的人.

entry.def: In the Anglican Church, a churchwarden is the person who has been chosen by a congregation to help the vicar of a parish with administration and other duties.

means.word_mean: 1. an officer in the Episcopal church who helps a parish priest with secular matters
